  "title": "The Cult of the Clitoris",
  "description": "London, 1918. The Great War is raging - and so is the trial of the century. Is a Canadian dancer guilty of treason, lesbianism, and treasonous lesbianism? Is Germany masterminding a sinister homosexual plot? And what exactly IS an orgasm? A scandalous true story of enmity, espionage, and eroticism.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Celia Taylor<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Celia Taylor and Tegan Siganski<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Timothy Anderson, Émanuel Dubbeldam, Rochelle Laplante, André Prevost, Maggie Salopek, Colby Stockdale, Rory Turner<br/>",
  "website": "https://empressofblandingsproductions.com",
  "plain_language": "The Cult of the Clitoris is based on a true story from 1918. A newspaper accused a famous dancer of being a lesbian and spying. She sued the newspaper for lying. The play shows the trial using real court transcripts and imagined talks outside the courtroom.",
